external_knowledge:
- Monikers refer to the names of the organizations;
- Financial support is synonymous with the grant amount awarded;
- Entities in this context are the organizations listed in the database.

sql:
SELECT T2.name, T1.grant_amount
FROM applications AS T1
INNER JOIN organizations AS T2 ON T1.ein = T2.ein;

SELECT DISTINCT name, organization_type
FROM organizations
WHERE organization_type = 'Non-profit';

external_knowledge:
- "reached the pinnacle of success" refers to applications marked as successful (is_successful = 1);
- "gold they have been crowned with" refers to the grant amount;
- The metaphor of "towering institutions" refers to the organizations;
- The top three in terms of the highest grant amounts are sought;
- "their names and addresses" refer to the organization's name and address.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(application_id) AS successful_application_count
FROM applications
WHERE is_successful = 1;
